## Constraints

- Execute exactly ONE step. Do not chain multiple steps.
- Verify after every sub-step. Do not proceed with known breakage.
- Revert immediately on verification failure — do not attempt fixes in this execution.
- Old code path must remain intact during CREATE and WIRE steps.
- Delete only during DELETE steps, and only after all consumers are verified.
- Do not execute arbitrary Python code in Jinja2 expressions (sandboxed execution).
- Handle missing variables gracefully (leave as-is or use default if specified).

